 SOURCE_URL_FULL=http://github.com/nrosvall/steel/archive/v$VERSION.tar.gz
      SOURCE_VFY=sha256:b6899e621d940a2e2d23e512ddb52734be83df2f4ea4eb7167e307c47135cbc4
        WEB_SITE=http://www.steelpasswordmanager.org/
         ENTERED=20160430
         UPDATED=20160430
           SHORT="Command line password manager"

cat << EOF
Steel is a password manager for GNU/Linux and comes with a GUI and a command
line version. With Steel your passwords are safe. Steel uses AES encryption
in CFB mode with 256 bit keys. Steel is simple, yet powerful.
Features:
  AES in CFB mode with 256 bit keys
  Uses bcrypt key derivation function with cost factor 12
  Fast and lightweight, written in C
  Both graphical and command line user interface
  Double click to copy password (GUI)
  Instant search, just start typing (GUI)
  Integrates with standard Unix tools
  Output is easy to parse (command line)
  Automatic clipboard clean up (GUI)
  Automatic database locking on idle (GUI)
  Uses SQLite, easy to write data importers from other password managers
  Backup and restore
  Verifies data integrity (timing safe)
  Manage multiple password databases with ease
  Generate secure passwords
  Shared library for easy development.
EOF
